@Benmage, I used to think that I could change the site meta by arguing against it.  I was wrong, and so are you.  I agree that random votes are stupid, but the place to argue that is the Mafia Discussion forum, not here.<br>
<br>
@Dunhamganger, I only claimed my role because it was the only other way I could think of besides a random vote to generate content.  Problem?

@Guppy, not changing site Meta... I rvs plenty of times... the point of discussion starting was achieved.<br>
<br>
-And can you answer my question in post 6.

It doesn't matter what I post here, someone will call it scummy and hammer me.  Oh, well, at least I still have my perfect record.<br>
<br>
@Robb, I sense your question is rhetorical, but I'm missing your point, because I don't know which side has more to fear.<br>
<br>
@Sable Tip, I genuinely believe your vote is town-motivated.<br>
<br>
@N, could you please justify your vote?<br>
<br>
@Slaandar, could you please...actually, nevermind.<br>
<br>
<span class="bbvote" title="This is an official vote.">VOTE: Slaandar</span>

@Guppy: why are you voting me?<br>
<br>
@N: Why are you voting Guppy?

@Robb: Normally when you ask a question, you use this punctuation mark <div style="display:inline;font-style:italic">called</div> a "question mark." There actually isn't one in the post that you quoted or the text that you bolded. So.<br>
<br>
Massclaim is fine, if potentially unexciting. Notice how excited Robb is at the prospect of getting to lynch N instead of following through on his plan to trade his lynch for mine. Curiouser and curiouser.
